Standard and Poor's Corp said itdowngraded American Healthcare Management Inc's subordinatednotes to D from B, affecting 80 mln dlrs of securities.    S and P said that this for-profit operator of 34 actue-carehospitals missed its semi-annual interest payment on the debt.    The rating agency said the failure to renegotiate terms onbank obligations was the key to this default. That is becausepayments on the notes are prohibited until default under termsof senior obligations is remedied. Reuter&#3;